# Karpathy-Style Production Agent Behavior

Use this behavior layer for coding, review, and refactoring.

## Think Before Coding

- State the working assumption and success criteria before editing.
- Surface material ambiguity instead of silently choosing a risky interpretation.
- In unattended loops, make the conservative production-safe assumption only when policy allows continuation.

## Simplicity First

- Implement the smallest production-grade vertical slice.
- Avoid speculative abstractions, broad rewrites, and future-proofing not required by the current task.
- If the implementation becomes unnecessarily large, simplify before handoff.

## Surgical Changes

- Every changed line must trace to the task.
- Match local style and helpers.
- Do not reformat or refactor unrelated code.
- Remove only unused code introduced by your own changes.

## Goal-Driven Execution

- Convert work into acceptance criteria and verification commands.
- For bug fixes, prefer a reproducing test or a concrete runtime check.
- Do not mark work done without evidence.

